(* Theorem: 0 < n ==> 2 ** (ulog n) < 2 * n /\ n <= 2 ** (ulog n) *)
(* Proof:
   Apply ulog_eqn, this is to show:
   (1) 1 < n ==> 2 ** SUC (LOG2 (n - 1)) < 2 * n
       Let m = n - 1.
       Note 0 < m                   by 1 < n
        ==> 2 ** LOG2 m <= m        by TWO_EXP_LOG2_LE, 0 < m
         or             <= n - 1    by notation
       Thus 2 ** LOG2 m < n         by inequality [1]
        and 2 ** SUC (LOG2 m)
          = 2 * 2 ** (LOG2 m)       by EXP
          < 2 * n                   by LT_MULT_LCANCEL, [1]
